node.text: @snowbreeeze i have listened to to the transmission and once again,the pilot seems to be the one at fault. Multiple times the atc requested for the clearance number and all the pilot repeated ‘standby’ lol. All that while flying over the country’s airspace

@aitothesyah seems. You are not sure. Secondly the transmission was cut OFF. What happened to the cut off portion? Thirdly the aircraft was handed over from RAN.  Why would Dhaka not ask for the adc number once handed over from RAN? Confusion amongst the ATC? Bangladesh is a poor country. I doubt the professionalism of the Bangladeshi ATC.
